<Layout title="Custom Enterprise Builds | Intelio - Enterprise Systems Integration at Scale" description="Enterprise-scale system integration. Multi-system architectures designed for your complexity. Built for regulatory compliance, massive scale, and competitive advantage.">
<main class="bg-white">
  <!-- ENHANCED HERO SECTION -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[90vh] flex items-center overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 via-slate-900 to-gray-900">
    <!-- Video Background -->
    <video 
      autoplay 
      loop 
      muted 
      playsinline
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover opacity-40"
    >
      <source src="/logos/Enterprise_Technology_Hero_Section_Video.mp4" type="video/mp4">
    </video>
    
    <!-- Gradient Overlay -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-gray-900/95 via-gray-900/80 to-gray-900/60 z-[1]"></div>
    
    <!-- Subtle noise texture -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.02] mix-blend-overlay z-[2]" style="background-image: url('data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg width=\'100\' height=\'100\' xmlns=\'http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\'%3E%3Cfilter id=\'noise\'%3E%3CfeTurbulence type=\'fractalNoise\' baseFrequency=\'0.9\' numOctaves=\'4\'/%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width=\'100%25\' height=\'100%25\' filter=\'url(%23noise)\'/%3E%3C/svg%3E');"></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 py-24 w-full">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <!-- Badge -->
        <div class="mb-6">
          <span class="text-blue-400 text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase">
            Enterprise Systems
          </span>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Headline -->
        <h1 class="text-5xl lg:text-7xl font-bold text-white leading-[1.1] mb-6 tracking-tight">
          Custom Enterprise Builds
        </h1>
        
        <!-- Subtitle -->
        <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-gray-200 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          When complexity is your competitive advantage.
        </p>
        
        <!-- Description -->
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-10 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
          You operate at scale. You have specialized requirements. Your competitive edge depends on systems built specifically for you‚Äînot generic software.<br><br>
          Off-the-shelf breaks at scale. Consultants recommend without building. Vendors overpromise.<br><br>
          You need a partner who engineers bespoke solutions and makes them work at scale.
        </p>
        
        <!-- CTAs -->
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="#what-we-build" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-500 text-white text-lg font-semibold rounded-xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl hover:scale-105 transition-all duration-300">
            Explore Enterprise Systems
            <svg class="ml-2 w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </a>
          <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 border-2 border-white/30 hover:border-white/60 text-white text-lg font-semibold rounded-xl hover:bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm transition-all duration-300">
            Schedule Enterprise Discovery
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Scroll indicator -->
    <div class="absolute bottom-8 left-1/2 transform -translate-x-1/2 z-10 animate-bounce">
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white/50" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 14l-7 7m0 0l-7-7m7 7V3"></path>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CREDIBILITY BAR -->
  <section class="py-12 px-6 bg-white border-b border-gray-100">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 font-medium">Trusted by operations leaders at:</p>
        <!-- Client Logos - Infinite Scroll -->
        <div class="logo-marquee-container w-full">
          <div class="logo-marquee-track">
            <!-- First set of logos -->
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/Newmark-logo.png" alt="Newmark" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium" style="display:none;">Newmark</span>
            </div>
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/hhp-grey-logo.png" alt="HHP" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium" style="display:none;">HHP</span>
            </div>
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/alliance-resource.png" alt="Alliance Resource Partners" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium text-sm" style="display:none;">Alliance Resource Partners</span>
            </div>
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/manhattan-construction-logo.png" alt="Manhattan Construction" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium text-sm" style="display:none;">Manhattan Construction</span>
            </div>
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/brain-body-soul-logo.png" alt="Brain Body Soul" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium text-sm" style="display:none;">Brain Body Soul</span>
            </div>
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/JLL-Logo.png" alt="JLL" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium" style="display:none;">JLL</span>
            </div>
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/CB logo.png" alt="CB" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium" style="display:none;">CB</span>
            </div>
            <!-- Duplicate set for seamless loop -->
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/Newmark-logo.png" alt="Newmark" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium" style="display:none;">Newmark</span>
            </div>
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/hhp-grey-logo.png" alt="HHP" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium" style="display:none;">HHP</span>
            </div>
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/alliance-resource.png" alt="Alliance Resource Partners" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium text-sm" style="display:none;">Alliance Resource Partners</span>
            </div>
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/manhattan-construction-logo.png" alt="Manhattan Construction" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium text-sm" style="display:none;">Manhattan Construction</span>
            </div>
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/brain-body-soul-logo.png" alt="Brain Body Soul" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium text-sm" style="display:none;">Brain Body Soul</span>
            </div>
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/JLL-Logo.png" alt="JLL" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium" style="display:none;">JLL</span>
            </div>
            <div class="logo-marquee-item">
              <img src="/logos/CB logo.png" alt="CB" class="logo-marquee-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block';">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium" style="display:none;">CB</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROBLEM SECTION -->
  <section class="problem-section py-20 md:py-24 px-6 bg-white relative">
    <!-- Left Accent Line (Animated) -->
    <div class="problem-accent-line absolute left-0 top-0 w-1 bg-blue-600 rounded-full z-10"></div>
    
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto relative z-10">
      <div class="mb-16 scroll-fade-in">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 inline-block pb-4 border-b-4 border-blue-600">
          The Limitations of Standard Approaches
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-600 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed mt-6 mb-12">
          Your organization is different. You've scaled beyond where standard software applies. Your complexity isn't a problem to solve‚Äîit's your competitive advantage. But standard solutions treat complexity as a liability.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-10 relative pl-8">
        <!-- Problem 1 -->
        <div class="problem-card bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-blue-50/30 rounded-lg p-8 border-t-4 border-l-4 border-blue-600 border-r border-b border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-500 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 scroll-fade-in">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="problem-icon flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 7h12m0 0l-4-4m4 4l-4 4m0 6H4m0 0l4 4m-4-4l4-4"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-3">Standard Software Wasn't Built for Your Scale</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Salesforce can handle 1,000 users. Then complexity builds, performance degrades, and you're fighting the platform, not using it. Airtable can handle 100,000 records. Then queries slow down, relationships become impossible, and you're hitting architectural limits. Standard software is built for the middle market. Slightly above that and it breaks.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Problem 2 -->
        <div class="problem-card bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-blue-50/30 rounded-lg p-8 border-t-4 border-l-4 border-blue-600 border-r border-b border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-500 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 scroll-fade-in">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="problem-icon flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6V4m0 2a2 2 0 100 4m0-4a2 2 0 110 4m-6 8a2 2 0 100-4m0 4a2 2 0 110-4m0 4v2m0-6V4m6 6v10m6-2a2 2 0 100-4m0 4a2 2 0 110-4m0 4v2m0-6V4"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-3">Integration Complexity Exposes the Fragmentation</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                You run on 5‚Äì7 major systems: CRM, accounting, operations, scheduling, data warehouse, internal tools, compliance systems. Each system is the "source of truth" for some data. None of them are the source of truth for everything. Data flows between systems are manual, incomplete, slow. Decision-making requires asking 5 different systems. Leadership doesn't get clarity because clarity doesn't exist.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Problem 3 -->
        <div class="problem-card bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-blue-50/30 rounded-lg p-8 border-t-4 border-l-4 border-blue-600 border-r border-b border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-500 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 scroll-fade-in">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="problem-icon flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M18.364 18.364A9 9 0 005.636 5.636m12.728 12.728A9 9 0 015.636 5.636m12.728 12.728L5.636 5.636"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-3">Legacy Systems Can't Be Replaced</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                You can't abandon systems that have 20 years of data and critical processes embedded in them. But you also can't build everything on top of legacy systems. You need new systems and old systems coexisting, integrated seamlessly. That integration is what vendors won't do. They want to be the only system.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Problem 4 -->
        <div class="problem-card bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-blue-50/30 rounded-lg p-8 border-t-4 border-l-4 border-blue-600 border-r border-b border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-500 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 scroll-fade-in">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="problem-icon flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-3">Specialized Requirements Need Specialized Solutions</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Your industry has specific compliance requirements. Your business model has unique workflows. Your competitive advantage depends on systems that work exactly like you work, not systems you adapt to. You need something built for your market. Not for everyone. For you.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Problem 5 -->
        <div class="problem-card bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-blue-50/30 rounded-lg p-8 border-t-4 border-l-4 border-blue-600 border-r border-b border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-500 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 scroll-fade-in">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="problem-icon flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7h8m0 0v8m0-8l-8 8-4-4-6 6"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-3">Off-the-Shelf Solutions Create Dependencies</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                You're not just dependent on the vendor's roadmap. You're dependent on their pricing decisions. Their feature prioritization. Their survival. If they get acquired, acquired out of your market, or shut down, you're stuck. Real competitive advantage requires owning your systems. Not renting them.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Problem 6 -->
        <div class="problem-card bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-blue-50/30 rounded-lg p-8 border-t-4 border-l-4 border-blue-600 border-r border-b border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-500 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 scroll-fade-in">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="problem-icon flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7h8m0 0v8m0-8l-8 8-4-4-6 6"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-3">Growth Creates Operational Chaos</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                You grew from $10M to $50M. The systems that worked at $10M don't work at $50M. Data volume breaks reporting. Team size breaks communication. Complexity breaks coordination. Scaling isn't just about adding revenue. It's about re-architecting how the organization operates. Most organizations fail at this transition.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Problem 7 -->
        <div class="problem-card bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-blue-50/30 rounded-lg p-8 border-t-4 border-l-4 border-blue-600 border-r border-b border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-500 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 scroll-fade-in">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="problem-icon flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-3">So You Manage Chaos Instead of Building Advantage</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                You accept fragmentation. You accept manual processes. You accept slow decision-making. You accept that growth requires organizational complexity. You manage chaos instead of building systems that prevent it. That's not a business strategy. That's surrender.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WE BUILD SECTION -->
  <section id="what-we-build" class="py-20 md:py-24 px-6 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Enterprise Systems Built for Your Specific Reality
        </h2>
        <div class="w-24 h-1 bg-blue-600 mx-auto mb-6"></div>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          We don't implement software. We engineer integrated platforms designed around how you operate, at your scale, with your complexity as the starting assumption.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="capability-cards-zigzag flex flex-col gap-6 max-w-5xl mx-auto relative">
        <!-- Center connector line -->
        <div class="hidden md:block absolute left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 w-0.5 bg-gradient-to-b from-blue-600 via-blue-400 to-gray-300 transform -translate-x-1/2 z-0"></div>
        
        <!-- Card 1: Left -->
        <div class="capability-card capability-card-zigzag-left relative z-10 w-[60%] max-w-[500px] bg-gradient-to-b from-white to-gray-50 rounded-xl p-10 border-t-2 border-r-3 border-blue-600 border-b border-l border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-500 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300 scroll-fade-in-stagger" style="animation-delay: 0ms;">
          <div class="relative mb-6">
            <div class="capability-badge absolute -top-2 -right-2 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">01</div>
            <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-100 to-blue-50 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center shadow-md hover:rotate-6 transition-transform duration-300">
              <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4 7v10c0 2.21 3.582 4 8 4s8-1.79 8-4V7M4 7c0 2.21 3.582 4 8 4s8-1.79 8-4M4 7c0-2.21 3.582-4 8-4s8 1.79 8 4m0 5c0 2.21-3.582 4-8 4s-8-1.79-8-4"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="h-0.5 w-12 bg-gray-200 mb-4"></div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-3">Connect Everything. Make Disparate Systems Operate as One.</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            You don't have one system. You have 5‚Äì10 systems all necessary, all containing critical data, none of them talking to each other. We build the integration layer that makes them operate as one. Data flows between systems automatically. Finance sees operational data real-time. Operations sees customer data real-time. Leadership sees unified reporting. You still have your legacy systems. You still have your specialized tools. But now they operate together instead of against each other.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 2: Right -->
        <div class="capability-card capability-card-zigzag-right relative z-10 w-[60%] max-w-[500px] ml-auto bg-gradient-to-b from-white to-gray-50 rounded-xl p-10 border-t-2 border-l-3 border-blue-600 border-r border-b border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-500 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300 scroll-fade-in-stagger" style="animation-delay: 100ms;">
          <div class="relative mb-6">
            <div class="capability-badge absolute -top-2 -right-2 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">02</div>
            <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-100 to-blue-50 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center shadow-md hover:rotate-6 transition-transform duration-300">
              <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="h-0.5 w-12 bg-gray-200 mb-4"></div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-3">Handle Enterprise-Scale Data Relationships</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Your data has relationships that simple databases can't handle. Deals have properties. Properties have buyers. Buyers have historical performance. Performance has patterns. Properties have markets. Markets have trends. Trends drive acquisition strategy. We design relational data architectures that capture this complexity. Query a deal and instantly see buyer fit, market conditions, and probability. Query a buyer and instantly see all relevant opportunities. Query a market and see supply/demand dynamics. This isn't possible with standard tools. It requires architectural sophistication.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 3: Left -->
        <div class="capability-card capability-card-zigzag-left relative z-10 w-[60%] max-w-[500px] bg-gradient-to-b from-white to-gray-50 rounded-xl p-10 border-t-2 border-r-3 border-blue-600 border-b border-l border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-500 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300 scroll-fade-in-stagger" style="animation-delay: 200ms;">
          <div class="relative mb-6">
            <div class="capability-badge absolute -top-2 -right-2 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">03</div>
